ading art academies and art test prep schools, Chumley combines ethnography and oral history with analyses of contemporary avant-garde and official art, popular media, and propaganda. Examining the rise of a Chinese artistic vanguard and creative knowledge-based economy, Creativity Class sheds light on an important facet of today's China.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aArt schoolszChina. 0aArtxStudy and teachingzChina. 0aArtsxStudy and teachingzChina. 0aDecorative artszChina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aArt Beijing.  aCentral Academy of Fine Arts.  aChina.  aChinese art students.  aChinese dreamworlds.  aReunion.  aaesthetic communities.  aaesthetic community.  aanomie.  aantinomies of class.  aart exhibitions.  aart school.  aart test prep realism.  aart test preparation classes.  aart test system.  aart test.  aartists.  aavant-garde realism.  acafs.  aclass recognition.  acreative class.  acreative human capital.  acreative practice.  acreativity classes.  acreativity industries.  acreativity.  acultural industries.  aculture workers.  adesigners.  aeducation policies.  afamily values.  afashion.  afine art.  agaigekaifang.  agraduates.  agraphic design.  ainstitutional history.  alinguistic anthropology.  aofficial state narratives.  apedagogical forms.  apedagogy.  apersonal subjectivity.  apolitical economy.  apolitical implications.  apolitical visions.  apostsocialism.  apostsocialist China.  apractice communities.  apracticing creativity.  aprofessional sites.  arealism.  arealist genres.  areform.  aself-styling.  asocialism.  asociality.  astudios.  aurban service economy.  avisual cultures.  aworking classes.08iTitle is part of eBook pack